==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ill-timed
<hw>Ill"-timed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Done, attempted,
or said, at an unsuitable or unpropitious time; occurring at an
inappropriate time; <as>as, an <ex>ill-timed</ex>
intervention</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ill timed(predicate), inappropriate, unseasonable,
untimely, wrong, poorly timed, badly timed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illtreat</ent>⟦br⟧
